1
00:00:12,106 --> 00:00:13,647
[speaking Cypriot Greek]

2
00:00:17,647 --> 00:00:19,189
[Fisk] This is a terrorist attack.

3
00:00:19,272 --> 00:00:23,272
Orchestrated and executed
by the vigilante of Hell's Kitchen.

4
00:00:27,231 --> 00:00:28,231
[Karen] I can't go with you.

5
00:00:28,314 --> 00:00:29,314
No, I know. I...

6
00:00:29,397 --> 00:00:31,231
-I didn't come to get you.
-Fucking great minds, huh?

7
00:00:31,314 --> 00:00:33,272
[Daredevil] He's gonna prosecute you
and humiliate you,

8
00:00:33,356 --> 00:00:34,897
and make everyone cheer for it.

9
00:00:34,981 --> 00:00:37,189
-[Karen] That means there'll be cameras.
-Exactly.

10
00:00:37,272 --> 00:00:38,814
[Kirsten] Can you tell me
about those scars?

11
00:00:38,897 --> 00:00:40,231
I got these in a firefight

12
00:00:40,314 --> 00:00:41,814
with Daredevil and Frank Castle.

13
00:00:41,897 --> 00:00:44,856
-[Kirsten] Was the defendant there?
-I was told she drove the getaway vehicle.

14
00:00:44,939 --> 00:00:47,856
You were told?
What else did Officer Powell tell you?

15
00:00:47,939 --> 00:00:49,689
-[gun fires]
-[crowd screams]

16
00:00:49,772 --> 00:00:51,564
Did he tell you to kill Hector Ayala?

17
00:00:53,106 --> 00:00:54,772
[Daredevil] You wanted
one good deed, right?

18
00:00:54,856 --> 00:00:56,064
[choking]

19
00:00:58,814 --> 00:01:00,814
[Dex] You know I can't make any promises.

20
00:01:01,272 --> 00:01:02,314
[Buck] Where is she?

21
00:01:03,272 --> 00:01:04,314
[Daniel] She's not coming.

22
00:01:05,189 --> 00:01:07,356
-[groans]
-Where, Daniel?

23
00:01:07,439 --> 00:01:11,731
How long till you're on the floor
with a gun pointed at your head?

24
00:01:22,856 --> 00:01:24,856
[♪ theme music playing]

25
00:03:03,606 --> 00:03:06,314
[♪ pensive music playing]

26
00:03:19,147 --> 00:03:21,856
[chattering indistinctly]

27
00:03:29,689 --> 00:03:31,939
-[judge] Miss McDuffie?
-[gavel bangs]

28
00:03:34,231 --> 00:03:35,897
[dial tone sounding]

29
00:03:35,981 --> 00:03:38,481
-Anything?
-Nope. No answer again.

30
00:03:38,564 --> 00:03:39,606
Shit.

31
00:03:39,689 --> 00:03:41,522
Is everything all right, Miss McDuffie?

32
00:03:42,189 --> 00:03:44,272
Will Mr. Murdock be joining us today?

33
00:03:44,356 --> 00:03:46,439
We're fine, Your Honor.
Please don't wait on us.

34
00:03:46,522 --> 00:03:51,106
Uh, Matt is tied up,
but he should be along shortly.

35
00:03:52,731 --> 00:03:56,064
[groans] God damn it, Jessica.

36
00:03:56,147 --> 00:03:57,856
-Oh, knock it off.
-[Matt winces]

37
00:03:58,981 --> 00:04:00,564
And you're not even that bad.

38
00:04:01,439 --> 00:04:04,022
[sighs] That's easy for you to say.
I'm not built like you.

39
00:04:04,106 --> 00:04:05,772
You've never tried childbirth.

40
00:04:06,522 --> 00:04:07,897
[chuckles]

41
00:04:08,731 --> 00:04:09,731
[winces]

42
00:04:09,814 --> 00:04:12,147
-You good?
-Yeah, I'm fine. I'm-- I'll be fine.

43
00:04:12,231 --> 00:04:13,231
Just need some...

44
00:04:14,564 --> 00:04:15,981
medication, some rest.

45
00:04:16,064 --> 00:04:17,981
Maybe a total knee replacement.

46
00:04:22,772 --> 00:04:24,272
You came back, huh?

47
00:04:24,356 --> 00:04:26,647
Thought you were done with Fisk.
With New York.

48
00:04:28,731 --> 00:04:30,564
This shit has gotten so far outta hand.

49
00:04:32,064 --> 00:04:33,106
I know.

50
00:04:33,564 --> 00:04:34,731
Can you stop him?

51
00:04:35,189 --> 00:04:36,397
Not alone.

52
00:04:37,814 --> 00:04:40,564
Well, that was kind of the idea.

53
00:04:40,647 --> 00:04:42,356
[Matt] I don't think
he's gonna kill Karen.

54
00:04:42,439 --> 00:04:44,647
At least,
not until he gets me in his sights.

55
00:04:46,689 --> 00:04:48,814
Which is exactly where I need to be.

56
00:04:52,647 --> 00:04:55,022
[knocking on door, door opens]

57
00:04:55,981 --> 00:04:57,064
Buck.

58
00:04:58,397 --> 00:04:59,481
Sir.

59
00:05:00,522 --> 00:05:04,606
Did Daniel deliver Miss Urich as promised?

60
00:05:07,106 --> 00:05:08,189
No.

61
00:05:19,731 --> 00:05:21,772
I think I'm only now understanding

62
00:05:21,856 --> 00:05:24,856
the responsibility of someone
who's elected by millions...

63
00:05:24,939 --> 00:05:28,397
chosen... by millions of New Yorkers.

64
00:05:32,939 --> 00:05:34,606
I hear the whispers.

65
00:05:37,439 --> 00:05:41,106
They think that my grief has clouded
my judgment. Do you believe that?

66
00:05:41,189 --> 00:05:42,272
No, sir.

67
00:05:46,689 --> 00:05:49,272
It seems Murdock has survived the night.

68
00:05:57,147 --> 00:05:58,522
[Buck] You really wanna do this?

69
00:06:04,314 --> 00:06:05,564
I will make arrangements.

70
00:06:06,897 --> 00:06:07,981
Thank you, Buck.

71
00:06:17,522 --> 00:06:19,106
[Heather] Her demeanor is combative.

72
00:06:19,189 --> 00:06:23,106
She exhibits the classic hallmarks
of antisocial personality disorder.

73
00:06:23,189 --> 00:06:25,689
Antisocial personality disorder.

74
00:06:25,772 --> 00:06:27,772
What we used to refer to as a sociopath?

75
00:06:27,856 --> 00:06:30,106
-Exactly.
-[door opens]

76
00:06:44,022 --> 00:06:46,689
Miss Page continues to unravel.

77
00:06:46,772 --> 00:06:50,439
In our interview last night,
she demonstrated hostility, duplicity--

78
00:06:50,522 --> 00:06:52,231
[Matt] Objection. It's prejudicial.

79
00:06:53,272 --> 00:06:55,939
Sidesteps any objective diagnosis
with conjecture.

80
00:06:56,022 --> 00:06:57,731
Mr. Hochberg, you know better.

81
00:06:57,814 --> 00:07:00,314
Mr. Murdock, are you okay?

82
00:07:01,064 --> 00:07:03,272
I am outstanding. Thank you, Your Honor.

83
00:07:04,106 --> 00:07:05,772
Mr. Hochberg, please continue.

84
00:07:06,731 --> 00:07:08,606
-Sorry I'm late.
-[whispers] Late?

85
00:07:08,689 --> 00:07:09,897
I thought you were dead.

86
00:07:09,981 --> 00:07:11,606
-Are you okay?
-Yeah, I'm fine.

87
00:07:11,689 --> 00:07:13,522
-Just got shot in the leg.
-[Hochberg] Dr. Glenn...

88
00:07:15,064 --> 00:07:16,689
I was wondering if you would
read to us a passage

89
00:07:16,772 --> 00:07:19,772
from your latest book, Men in Masks.

90
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:22,689
"The Psychology of Vigilantes."

91
00:07:23,147 --> 00:07:26,897
Especially interested
in Chapter 2, page 35.

92
00:07:28,231 --> 00:07:29,314
Of course.

93
00:07:30,606 --> 00:07:33,939
"The vigilante's mask
does not hide his public face,

94
00:07:34,689 --> 00:07:37,397
"in fact, it reveals his private face.

95
00:07:37,481 --> 00:07:40,522
"The real mask is the one
that he wears in his public life.

96
00:07:40,606 --> 00:07:44,147
"The dutiful boyfriend,
the responsible boss...

97
00:07:45,981 --> 00:07:47,356
"the loyal son."

98
00:07:48,689 --> 00:07:51,772
Thank you so much. No further questions.

99
00:07:53,647 --> 00:07:54,772
Your witness.

100
00:07:59,439 --> 00:08:00,939
So, let me get this straight.

101
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:05,481
You said, "The real mask is the face
the vigilante wears in public," right?

102
00:08:05,564 --> 00:08:10,647
The son, the boss, the boyfriend...
Maybe even the clinical professional?

103
00:08:11,481 --> 00:08:12,564
Is that a question?

104
00:08:13,397 --> 00:08:17,022
Dr. Glenn, did you strike Miss Page
during your evaluation last night?

105
00:08:17,106 --> 00:08:19,272
-[Hochberg] Objection.
-Absolutely not.

106
00:08:19,356 --> 00:08:21,064
-Sustained.
-No further questions.

107
00:08:22,481 --> 00:08:23,814
[scoffs]

108
00:08:23,897 --> 00:08:25,314
Actually, I have a question.

109
00:08:25,897 --> 00:08:28,689
Dr. Glenn, does...
does a vigilante need a mask?

110
00:08:29,689 --> 00:08:32,772
-How do you mean, specifically?
-In your professional opinion,

111
00:08:32,856 --> 00:08:36,439
would my client qualify as a vigilante
if she never cultivated an alter ego?

112
00:08:36,522 --> 00:08:38,689
-Or, as you call it, a mask?
-Sure.

113
00:08:38,772 --> 00:08:39,939
She didn't need a mask.

114
00:08:41,022 --> 00:08:42,939
She hid behind Daredevil's.

115
00:08:44,064 --> 00:08:46,314
In the same way that you're hiding
behind the Fisk administration.

116
00:08:46,397 --> 00:08:47,981
-[Hochberg] Objection.
-[judge] Sustained.

117
00:08:49,981 --> 00:08:52,314
I see. Thank you. No further questions.

118
00:08:52,397 --> 00:08:54,064
[judge] The court is recessed for lunch.

119
00:08:54,147 --> 00:08:55,314
When we return,

120
00:08:55,397 --> 00:08:57,606
-the defense can call its first witness.
-[gavel bangs]

121
00:09:04,481 --> 00:09:07,981
[man chattering indistinctly
over radio]

122
00:09:08,064 --> 00:09:10,064
[camera beeping]

123
00:09:46,772 --> 00:09:47,814
[Judge Grimes] Mmm-hmm.

124
00:09:47,897 --> 00:09:49,772
And the prosecution has no objections?

125
00:09:49,856 --> 00:09:51,314
Oh, far from it, Your Honors.

126
00:09:51,397 --> 00:09:53,564
We welcome Mr. Murdock's self-sabotage.

127
00:09:54,272 --> 00:09:56,522
-I'll allow it.
-Thank you, Your Honor.

128
00:09:57,481 --> 00:09:58,522
Call your witness.

129
00:10:01,606 --> 00:10:04,106
The defense calls Mayor Wilson Fisk.

130
00:10:04,939 --> 00:10:06,939
[audience murmuring indistinctly]

131
00:10:09,064 --> 00:10:12,481
[♪ dramatic opera music playing]

132
00:10:26,439 --> 00:10:27,939
[bailiff] Raise your right hand.

133
00:10:28,981 --> 00:10:31,897
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth,

134
00:10:31,981 --> 00:10:33,939
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?

135
00:10:34,856 --> 00:10:36,231
[heart thumping]

136
00:10:38,481 --> 00:10:39,481
I do.

137
00:10:41,064 --> 00:10:42,564
State your full name.

138
00:10:43,189 --> 00:10:44,981
Wilson Grant Fisk.

139
00:11:08,397 --> 00:11:10,731
[whispering indistinctly]

140
00:11:18,022 --> 00:11:20,772
You know, when I was a boy...

141
00:11:22,564 --> 00:11:25,231
I was taught to find
the biggest man, and...

142
00:11:27,231 --> 00:11:28,481
bring him down.

143
00:11:32,314 --> 00:11:36,814
But as I grew, I realized
that no man stands as tall

144
00:11:37,481 --> 00:11:38,564
as this courthouse,

145
00:11:40,564 --> 00:11:42,439
these institutions.

146
00:11:46,731 --> 00:11:50,564
[clears throat]
That was lovely, Mr. Mayor.

147
00:11:50,647 --> 00:11:52,606
Thank you for joining us today.

148
00:11:52,689 --> 00:11:55,939
Not at all. I consider it my civic duty,
and I welcome the opportunity

149
00:11:56,022 --> 00:12:00,147
to see my Safer Streets Initiative
in action, to see justice prevail.

150
00:12:00,231 --> 00:12:02,189
[Matt] I was a little surprised
you, uh, showed up.

151
00:12:02,272 --> 00:12:03,897
I could say the same for you.

152
00:12:04,814 --> 00:12:06,106
Thank you. I'll live.

153
00:12:33,189 --> 00:12:34,939
[screams, grunts]

154
00:12:35,814 --> 00:12:37,147
[screams]

155
00:12:39,481 --> 00:12:41,231
[breathing heavily]

156
00:12:50,314 --> 00:12:52,314
[chuckles softly]

157
00:12:54,939 --> 00:12:56,189
Argh!

158
00:12:57,606 --> 00:12:58,606
God!

159
00:12:58,689 --> 00:13:00,231
Fuck!

160
00:13:00,856 --> 00:13:02,189
[groans]

161
00:13:08,064 --> 00:13:09,147
Fuck!

162
00:13:12,189 --> 00:13:13,189
[Bullseye chuckles]

163
00:13:17,064 --> 00:13:18,147
Poseur.

164
00:13:24,481 --> 00:13:28,231
The Safer Streets Initiative
was born out of necessity.

165
00:13:28,314 --> 00:13:33,856
It was created to save lives,
lives destroyed by vigilante violence.

166
00:13:36,981 --> 00:13:38,856
It's too late for Foggy Nelson. It's...

167
00:13:39,856 --> 00:13:44,314
too late for Muse's victims,
for Officer Saunders.

168
00:13:50,106 --> 00:13:54,189
And, uh, my wife, Vanessa.

169
00:13:55,356 --> 00:14:01,022
But we can bring these criminals,
like Karen Page and Daredevil, to justice.

170
00:14:04,731 --> 00:14:06,939
People we lost deserve that.

171
00:14:07,022 --> 00:14:08,439
People of New York...

172
00:14:09,314 --> 00:14:10,397
deserve that.

173
00:14:15,064 --> 00:14:17,814
I'm sorry, was that an answer
or a speech, Mr. Mayor?

174
00:14:18,731 --> 00:14:21,731
You asked me why I enacted
the Safer Streets Initiative.

175
00:14:21,814 --> 00:14:24,106
You, of all people, should know.
You were there.

176
00:14:24,189 --> 00:14:25,481
Ah, I see. Yes.

177
00:14:25,564 --> 00:14:27,147
When Bullseye took a shot at you--

178
00:14:27,231 --> 00:14:29,272
Actually, you called me a hero
that night, didn't you?

179
00:14:29,356 --> 00:14:31,856
Objection. Can we have
a little relevance, please?

180
00:14:31,939 --> 00:14:33,772
Sustained. Get to the point, Counselor.

181
00:14:33,856 --> 00:14:35,897
My point is that,
as the mayor stated before,

182
00:14:35,981 --> 00:14:38,022
the statute that my client
is being charged under

183
00:14:38,106 --> 00:14:41,064
was supposedly created to protect the city
from criminal vigilantes.

184
00:14:41,147 --> 00:14:43,731
-Is that a fair assessment, Mr. Mayor?
-It is.

185
00:14:44,231 --> 00:14:45,647
And are the streets safer?

186
00:14:46,939 --> 00:14:49,231
Statistics say they are, yes.

187
00:14:50,064 --> 00:14:51,647
But there is still lawlessness...

188
00:14:51,731 --> 00:14:52,731
Of course.

189
00:14:52,814 --> 00:14:54,397
I mean, some might say, rounding people up

190
00:14:54,481 --> 00:14:56,814
and throwing them into detention
without due process is lawless.

191
00:14:56,897 --> 00:14:59,314
Objection. Immaterial. Invites conjecture.

192
00:14:59,397 --> 00:15:00,397
Sustained.

193
00:15:00,481 --> 00:15:02,147
-Your Honor, I'll rephrase.
-Thank you.

194
00:15:03,189 --> 00:15:06,439
Mr. Mayor, your policies,
as harsh as they may be,

195
00:15:06,522 --> 00:15:08,147
did not prevent
a criminal from taking a shot at you

196
00:15:08,231 --> 00:15:09,647
and, ultimately, murdering your wife.

197
00:15:09,731 --> 00:15:11,731
An assassin, actually,
who I believe was once in your employ.

198
00:15:11,814 --> 00:15:14,939
Objection. This is contemptible,
even for Counselor Murdock.

199
00:15:15,022 --> 00:15:17,314
Sustained. This kitchen sink approach
is getting tedious.

200
00:15:17,397 --> 00:15:18,647
Your Honor, there is a point to all this.

201
00:15:18,731 --> 00:15:20,897
Please remember what my colleague
asked at the beginning of this trial.

202
00:15:20,981 --> 00:15:23,022
"What is a vigilante? What is a criminal?"

203
00:15:24,314 --> 00:15:25,606
Please.

204
00:15:26,939 --> 00:15:29,272
You really wanna do this, Mr. Murdock?

205
00:15:29,856 --> 00:15:31,522
Oh, absolutely, sir.

206
00:15:35,356 --> 00:15:37,772
Karen Page is charged with,
among many other crimes,

207
00:15:37,856 --> 00:15:39,814
aiding Daredevil in the sinking
of the Northern Star,

208
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:41,397
resulting in the death of its crew.

209
00:15:41,481 --> 00:15:43,564
Mister Fisk, were you aware
that the Northern Star

210
00:15:43,647 --> 00:15:46,314
is smuggling illegal arms into
New York City via the free port

211
00:15:46,397 --> 00:15:48,397
that is owned
by the Fisk Industries Trust?

212
00:15:48,481 --> 00:15:50,606
Objection. Assumes evidence
not on the record.

213
00:15:50,689 --> 00:15:51,939
Sustained.

214
00:15:53,481 --> 00:15:54,481
[chuckles] Yeah.

215
00:16:00,272 --> 00:16:03,022
Mr. Mayor,
did Daredevil sink the Northern Star?

216
00:16:05,022 --> 00:16:06,856
The evidence says yes.

217
00:16:07,481 --> 00:16:09,439
No, it doesn't.
The evidence does not suggest that.

218
00:16:09,522 --> 00:16:12,022
The only thing that's been presented
is testimony from Officer Powell,

219
00:16:12,106 --> 00:16:14,647
who is in your employ,
who takes his orders from you.

220
00:16:14,731 --> 00:16:16,314
It is the allegation
of the District Attorney,

221
00:16:16,397 --> 00:16:19,064
who, guess what, is in your employ,
takes his orders from you.

222
00:16:19,147 --> 00:16:21,022
-[Hochberg] Objection.
-Overruled.

223
00:16:24,147 --> 00:16:25,481
Your Honor, at this point, I would like to

224
00:16:25,564 --> 00:16:27,356
introduce evidence regarding
the Northern Star.

225
00:16:27,439 --> 00:16:30,439
Video testimony from the ship's
first mate, Christofi Savva.

226
00:16:30,522 --> 00:16:32,647
-[Hochberg] Objection. Video testimony?
-Overruled.

227
00:16:32,731 --> 00:16:36,689
Mr. Savva was duly deposed
by Miss McDuffie before he "disappeared."

228
00:16:36,772 --> 00:16:38,189
Considering the flexible standards

229
00:16:38,272 --> 00:16:39,606
of this court,
such evidence should be admissible.

230
00:16:39,689 --> 00:16:42,064
-Christ, this is turning into a circus.
-Mr. Hochberg,

231
00:16:42,147 --> 00:16:44,564
I think we've been
under the big top for a while now.

232
00:16:44,647 --> 00:16:46,272
I'd like to see counselors in chambers.

233
00:16:47,022 --> 00:16:50,189
Mr. Savva's testimony is substantial
and relevant in and of itself.

234
00:16:50,272 --> 00:16:52,022
-The man's not even present in court.
-It doesn't matter that he's not present.

235
00:16:52,106 --> 00:16:53,522
-And relevant to what?
-It-- What--

236
00:16:54,106 --> 00:16:55,231
[Fisk] Murdock...

237
00:16:57,147 --> 00:17:00,064
There are things I can say in here
that will ruin your life.

238
00:17:00,147 --> 00:17:03,356
With the complete support
of the legal system,

239
00:17:04,356 --> 00:17:07,356
I can have you thrown in a cell forever.

240
00:17:07,897 --> 00:17:10,106
I could say the same about you.

241
00:17:11,272 --> 00:17:12,564
-Excuse me?
-Hmm?

242
00:17:13,606 --> 00:17:15,689
No, about relevance, Your Honor.

243
00:17:15,772 --> 00:17:18,481
Karen Page is charged with
providing support to terrorist attacks.

244
00:17:18,564 --> 00:17:20,731
It's the definition of relevance
that the defense provide

245
00:17:20,814 --> 00:17:22,814
exculpatory evidence
about one such attack.

246
00:17:22,897 --> 00:17:25,606
And a basis for appeal
if such evidence is suppressed.

247
00:17:25,689 --> 00:17:27,564
There's not going to be any appeal.

248
00:17:27,647 --> 00:17:30,731
[chuckles] You're saying that out loud
in front of the judges?

249
00:17:30,814 --> 00:17:32,981
You wanna just hand Fisk
the robes and gavel?

250
00:17:35,939 --> 00:17:37,022
We'll allow it.

251
00:17:37,856 --> 00:17:38,939
Thank you.

252
00:17:41,564 --> 00:17:44,147
My name is Christofi Savva.

253
00:17:44,731 --> 00:17:47,314
I was the first mate on the Northern Star.

254
00:17:47,897 --> 00:17:52,022
We were under orders to sink the ship
if it was ever boarded.

255
00:17:52,106 --> 00:17:53,522
[McDuffie] Why was that?

256
00:17:55,439 --> 00:17:58,147
[Christofi] Because the Northern Star
was carrying weapons,

257
00:17:58,231 --> 00:18:00,564
military grade, very illegal.

258
00:18:01,064 --> 00:18:04,064
[McDuffie] Who sank the Northern Star,
Mr. Savva?

259
00:18:04,147 --> 00:18:06,939
[Christofi] My captain,
Achilleo Kyriaco.

260
00:18:07,022 --> 00:18:08,314
[McDuffie] Not Daredevil?

261
00:18:09,064 --> 00:18:10,689
[Christofi] Not Daredevil.

262
00:18:11,606 --> 00:18:13,064
[McDuffie] But he was there?

263
00:18:13,147 --> 00:18:14,689
Yes. He found the weapons.

264
00:18:14,772 --> 00:18:17,272
[McDuffie] And who is was the one
who ordered you to scuttle the ship?

265
00:18:17,356 --> 00:18:20,314
[Christofi] Achilleo has called him...
[speaking Cypriot Greek]

266
00:18:21,189 --> 00:18:22,272
[in English] ...the Kingpin...

267
00:18:23,564 --> 00:18:25,856
but we knew it was the Mayor.

268
00:18:26,606 --> 00:18:29,314
-Wilson Fisk.
-[gavel bangs]

269
00:18:29,397 --> 00:18:31,439
-[Justice Waters] Order! Order!
-[Hochberg] Your Honors,

270
00:18:31,522 --> 00:18:33,647
the witness we just heard from
is not in court.

271
00:18:33,731 --> 00:18:35,772
As such, his testimony remains immaterial,

272
00:18:35,856 --> 00:18:39,814
unless it can be corroborated by someone
who was actually on the Northern Star.

273
00:18:39,897 --> 00:18:41,981
And that is exactly
what I intend to do, Your Honors.

274
00:18:42,064 --> 00:18:43,981
Then please, by all means, do so.

275
00:18:44,564 --> 00:18:48,397
Mr. Mayor, through evidence testimony
in your own statements,

276
00:18:48,481 --> 00:18:51,564
we have determined that Daredevil
was on the Northern Star, correct?

277
00:18:51,647 --> 00:18:53,314
It's safe to say.

278
00:18:53,397 --> 00:18:56,147
So, if only we could ask him
what he witnessed that night.

279
00:18:57,772 --> 00:19:01,147
I welcome going down this road
with you, Mr. Murdock.

280
00:19:01,564 --> 00:19:02,564
As do I.

281
00:19:03,772 --> 00:19:07,022
Is it safe to say
you don't really like Daredevil?

282
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:10,231
Safe to say, yes.

283
00:19:11,064 --> 00:19:13,272
But what if the people of New York
disagree with you, sir?

284
00:19:13,356 --> 00:19:15,814
What if the public actually think
that Daredevil is a hero?

285
00:19:15,897 --> 00:19:20,147
[laughs] The people know better.

286
00:19:21,189 --> 00:19:22,189
Do they?

287
00:19:23,439 --> 00:19:26,439
I mean, I guess it depends
on how you define a hero.

288
00:19:27,106 --> 00:19:29,772
Take me, for example.
I took a bullet for you, didn't I?

289
00:19:29,856 --> 00:19:31,064
Would that make me a hero?

290
00:19:31,147 --> 00:19:34,647
[audience murmuring indistinctly]

291
00:19:36,189 --> 00:19:38,481
[cameras snapping]

292
00:19:49,106 --> 00:19:51,189
It's a simple yes or no question, sir.

293
00:19:51,731 --> 00:19:52,772
Am I a hero?

294
00:19:52,856 --> 00:19:55,189
[Hochberg] I'm sorry, Your Honors,
what does any of this nonsense

295
00:19:55,272 --> 00:19:56,564
have to do with Karen Page?

296
00:19:56,647 --> 00:20:00,814
Who, I remind you, is the only person,
as of now, on trial here today.

297
00:20:00,897 --> 00:20:03,439
My client's being tried in a court
created by one man,

298
00:20:03,522 --> 00:20:05,564
who has an obsession with one vigilante

299
00:20:05,647 --> 00:20:08,147
a vigilante who sent him to prison
on more than one occasion.

300
00:20:08,231 --> 00:20:09,481
[Justice Waters] Mister Murdock,
we allowed you

301
00:20:09,564 --> 00:20:11,022
admission of the video testimony.

302
00:20:11,106 --> 00:20:13,022
-Use it or lose it. Please. Now.
-[Matt] With pleasure.

303
00:20:13,106 --> 00:20:14,939
Mister Fisk, did you or did you not

304
00:20:15,022 --> 00:20:17,147
orchestrate the sale
of military-grade weapons

305
00:20:17,231 --> 00:20:18,814
through the official use of your office,

306
00:20:18,897 --> 00:20:21,897
and then order the Northern Star
to be scuttled when your plan was exposed?

307
00:20:21,981 --> 00:20:23,606
-Do not answer that, sir.
-Why not answer it?

308
00:20:23,689 --> 00:20:25,022
-Do not answer it.
-Answer it, sir.

309
00:20:25,106 --> 00:20:26,856
[yells] I will answer it!

310
00:20:26,939 --> 00:20:28,314
[audience gasps, murmurs]

311
00:20:30,814 --> 00:20:33,064
You don't get to know
what comes through our port.

312
00:20:35,439 --> 00:20:38,564
All you need to know is that
I'm running this city and it's thriving.

313
00:20:38,647 --> 00:20:42,106
Anything else is
above your paygrade, little man.

314
00:20:42,189 --> 00:20:45,189
Your... Your video proves no wrongdoing
by the mayor, Murdock. It's all hearsay.

315
00:20:45,272 --> 00:20:48,356
Correct, but we have established there was
another witness on that boat, haven't we?

316
00:20:48,439 --> 00:20:50,856
A witness who, in fact,
is in this courtroom today.

317
00:20:50,939 --> 00:20:53,522
-Isn't that right, Mr. Mayor?
-[audience gasps, murmurs]

318
00:20:56,814 --> 00:20:58,606
You and I both know who Daredevil is.

319
00:20:58,689 --> 00:21:01,064
He's the man who knows exactly
what happened on the Northern Star.

320
00:21:01,147 --> 00:21:03,397
He knows exactly
what happened in my apartment,

321
00:21:03,481 --> 00:21:07,356
and he knows exactly who the real criminal
in this courtroom is. Isn't that right?

322
00:21:13,814 --> 00:21:14,856
[grunts]

323
00:21:15,939 --> 00:21:17,106
You are a fool.

324
00:21:22,814 --> 00:21:24,272
No, I'm not.

325
00:21:26,064 --> 00:21:28,147
-I am Daredevil.
-[audience gasps, murmurs]

326
00:21:28,939 --> 00:21:31,147
[Hochberg] But-- Objection.

327
00:21:32,356 --> 00:21:33,731
-Objection!
-[Justice Waters] Order!

328
00:21:33,814 --> 00:21:35,856
-[Hochberg] Your Honors, this is insane.
-[Justice Waters] Order!

329
00:21:35,939 --> 00:21:37,856
-[Justice Waters] Order! Order.
-[gavel banging]

330
00:21:38,356 --> 00:21:39,981
-Order, please!
-[Hochberg] Representing a criminal?

331
00:21:40,064 --> 00:21:41,481
What is this?

332
00:21:43,272 --> 00:21:45,981
Are you, honestly,
going to tell this court

333
00:21:46,064 --> 00:21:49,814
-that Daredevil is a blind man?
-[audience gasps]

334
00:21:56,314 --> 00:21:57,772
Order. Order!

335
00:21:58,272 --> 00:21:59,897
A blind lawyer who can fight.

336
00:21:59,981 --> 00:22:01,731
-[Justice Waters] Order, please!
-[Hochberg] This is an absolute farce!

337
00:22:01,814 --> 00:22:04,022
The Northern Star
smuggled weapons into the city

338
00:22:04,106 --> 00:22:06,064
-under orders from Mayor Fisk. I was--
-Objection!

339
00:22:06,147 --> 00:22:07,981
-I was there and can testify to this.
-Overruled!

340
00:22:08,064 --> 00:22:11,439
Miss Jones and myself then
witnessed Fisk arm his private militia,

341
00:22:11,522 --> 00:22:13,647
A.K.A. the task force, with said weapons.

342
00:22:13,731 --> 00:22:16,356
Which we then destroyed
in the interest of public safety.

343
00:22:16,939 --> 00:22:18,397
Fisk's smuggling is a criminal act.

344
00:22:18,481 --> 00:22:20,772
Arming the task force with
smuggled weapons is a criminal act.

345
00:22:20,856 --> 00:22:23,439
Enough evidence has been provided
to charge Fisk with these crimes.

346
00:22:23,522 --> 00:22:24,981
-But first-- I'm not finished!
-Are you really--

347
00:22:25,064 --> 00:22:27,606
-Overruled.
-Your Honor, this court was formed

348
00:22:27,689 --> 00:22:29,647
to adjudicate
the Safer Streets Initiative,

349
00:22:29,731 --> 00:22:32,106
an initiative created
by this man, Mayor Fisk,

350
00:22:32,189 --> 00:22:34,564
in furtherance of his criminal agenda!

351
00:22:35,147 --> 00:22:37,772
Which means, this court has
neither the ability nor the mandate

352
00:22:37,856 --> 00:22:40,522
-to decide justice!
-[audience cheers]

353
00:22:40,606 --> 00:22:43,897
-[gavel bangs]
-[Justice Waters] Order. Order! Please!

354
00:23:01,772 --> 00:23:03,689
Daredevil or not, Mr. Murdock is right.

355
00:23:03,772 --> 00:23:07,939
In light of the evidence,
the corroborated testimony,

356
00:23:08,022 --> 00:23:10,772
Miss Page's crimes,
if they even are crimes,

357
00:23:10,856 --> 00:23:12,772
cannot be judged by this court.

358
00:23:12,856 --> 00:23:15,064
Thank you, Your Honor.
I move for dismissal.

359
00:23:15,147 --> 00:23:17,606
Granted. This case is dismissed
with prejudice.

360
00:23:17,689 --> 00:23:19,481
Miss Page, you're free to go.

361
00:23:19,564 --> 00:23:21,731
Mr. Murdock,
please remain in the courthouse.

362
00:23:21,814 --> 00:23:24,481
[applauding and cheering]

363
00:23:26,106 --> 00:23:27,189
Oh, thank God.

364
00:23:42,481 --> 00:23:44,856
You've won nothing, Mr. Murdock.

365
00:23:45,731 --> 00:23:46,731
Nothing.

366
00:23:52,064 --> 00:23:55,939
Mr. Fisk, the attorney general
has filed charges against you,

367
00:23:56,022 --> 00:24:01,064
for racketeering, smuggling, corruption...
at this point, it's a dictionary.

368
00:24:01,147 --> 00:24:02,772
Your assets have been frozen,

369
00:24:02,856 --> 00:24:05,481
and the free port
is under government control.

370
00:24:05,564 --> 00:24:08,397
On the word of a deluded lawyer?
None of it will stand up.

371
00:24:08,481 --> 00:24:12,064
Oh, then there's attempted murder
against a government official.

372
00:24:13,106 --> 00:24:15,397
Your assassin lived. He has a lot to say.

373
00:24:16,731 --> 00:24:18,731
This is the part where you resign.

374
00:24:18,814 --> 00:24:20,731
[Fisk] There's a process
for what you propose.

375
00:24:20,814 --> 00:24:23,147
I suggest you start that up.

376
00:24:23,231 --> 00:24:24,481
If you'll excuse me...

377
00:24:26,481 --> 00:24:31,147
Interesting to see who you've
aligned yourself with, Miss Jones.

378
00:24:31,647 --> 00:24:34,147
Watch yourself, Kingpin.

379
00:24:37,147 --> 00:24:38,897
[reporters chattering indistinctly]

380
00:24:43,606 --> 00:24:45,564
Where are you going, Daredevil?

381
00:24:47,356 --> 00:24:48,481
You're going to hide?

382
00:24:49,356 --> 00:24:51,272
Accept defeat gracefully, old man.

383
00:24:52,147 --> 00:24:55,022
Matthew Murdock, Daredevil...

384
00:24:55,106 --> 00:24:57,689
[Fisk] Defeat?
You've only weakened yourself.

385
00:24:57,772 --> 00:24:59,314
[Matt] It's over. You lost the city.

386
00:24:59,814 --> 00:25:02,022
-I've lost nothing.
-Murdock's coming out. Prepare the shot.

387
00:25:02,106 --> 00:25:05,272
-Repeat, prepare to take the shot.
-[Bullseye] Sorry, pal. Wrong Bullseye.

388
00:25:05,356 --> 00:25:06,481
-[Powell] Sir, it's a trap!
-No-- Wait!

389
00:25:06,564 --> 00:25:07,772
You don't, you don't wanna do that!
You don't--

390
00:25:07,897 --> 00:25:09,106
-[gun fires]
-[Powell] Outta here!

391
00:25:09,189 --> 00:25:11,272
-Get him the fuck outta here! Go, go, go!
-[crowd gasps]

392
00:25:12,772 --> 00:25:15,772
Get the mayor out of here
and don't let Murdock leave the building!

393
00:25:20,439 --> 00:25:23,814
Get fire in that top right window!
Get fire in that top right window!

394
00:25:23,897 --> 00:25:25,606
Go! Move!

395
00:25:28,272 --> 00:25:29,564
[all screaming]

396
00:25:33,856 --> 00:25:37,272
-Here.
-[Buck panting]

397
00:25:39,064 --> 00:25:40,064
[officer] Secure the doors.

398
00:25:44,231 --> 00:25:47,064
As you can see behind me,
a surreal scene is unfolding

399
00:25:47,147 --> 00:25:50,939
outside the courthouse as Mayor Fisk
has locked down the building

400
00:25:51,022 --> 00:25:54,814
in the wake of the explosive end
to the trial of Karen Page.

401
00:25:54,897 --> 00:25:58,814
Defense attorney Matt Murdock
shocked the courtroom with his admission

402
00:25:58,897 --> 00:26:02,064
that he is the vigilante known
as Daredevil.

403
00:26:02,147 --> 00:26:03,272
[Kirsten] What is he waiting for?

404
00:26:03,356 --> 00:26:06,522
I don't know. We can't just hold up here.
I mean, we're sitting ducks.

405
00:26:06,606 --> 00:26:08,772
Yes. God bless jurisprudence.

406
00:26:08,856 --> 00:26:11,314
Task force or not, at this point,
he just wants to tear it all down.

407
00:26:11,397 --> 00:26:13,147
-I'm calling in the National Guard.
-Wait.

408
00:26:14,022 --> 00:26:15,022
There's more.

409
00:26:29,106 --> 00:26:32,522
New York is in a state of emergency.

410
00:26:34,647 --> 00:26:38,856
Following today's miscarriage of justice,

411
00:26:38,939 --> 00:26:41,106
we were once again
attacked by a vigilante.

412
00:26:41,189 --> 00:26:44,481
My aide has been wounded.

413
00:26:45,897 --> 00:26:46,897
[grunts]

414
00:26:48,689 --> 00:26:52,439
Right now, we are under siege.

415
00:26:53,189 --> 00:26:57,481
As we speak, our enemies are assembling.

416
00:26:59,439 --> 00:27:00,439
Masked,

417
00:27:01,314 --> 00:27:04,022
hidden, and they're coming for all of us.

418
00:27:05,147 --> 00:27:07,606
I want to make myself clear to you.

419
00:27:09,522 --> 00:27:11,522
I will not abandon you.

420
00:27:13,606 --> 00:27:14,689
I swore an oath,

421
00:27:15,606 --> 00:27:17,314
and I intend to honor it.

422
00:27:19,772 --> 00:27:22,981
I will stand and fight.

423
00:27:26,647 --> 00:27:27,647
Will you?

424
00:27:29,481 --> 00:27:32,439
Jesus Christ. He's asking for a war.

425
00:27:32,522 --> 00:27:33,606
See, that's my concern.

426
00:27:33,689 --> 00:27:36,356
You call in the National Guard,
you're giving him exactly what he wants.

427
00:27:36,439 --> 00:27:38,731
Yeah, then, that'll take hours. I mean,
we, we have to stop this now.

428
00:27:38,814 --> 00:27:40,939
-Hold on one second.
-[Karen] What?

429
00:27:42,272 --> 00:27:45,897
-[♪ fanfare playing]
-Hello. It's me again.

430
00:27:45,981 --> 00:27:51,439
We are under siege. By me.
[giggles]

431
00:27:51,522 --> 00:27:55,481
-[tape distorts]
-[BB] The mayor's right.

432
00:27:57,147 --> 00:27:59,356
We are under siege.

433
00:27:59,439 --> 00:28:01,106
-[man] Stop!
-[officer] Push them back!

434
00:28:02,314 --> 00:28:03,731
[BB] By the task force.

435
00:28:04,564 --> 00:28:08,314
By the people
who kill our family, and our friends,

436
00:28:09,064 --> 00:28:10,189
and lock us up.

437
00:28:11,897 --> 00:28:14,147
[echoing] It's our city, not his.

438
00:28:15,356 --> 00:28:16,397
It's time...

439
00:28:17,856 --> 00:28:18,897
to take it back.

440
00:28:21,272 --> 00:28:23,106
-[woman 1] Slide through. Come on.
-[woman 2] Come on!

441
00:28:23,189 --> 00:28:24,189
[man] Move out, move out.

442
00:28:26,772 --> 00:28:27,939
[group] Go. Quiet, quiet.

443
00:28:33,647 --> 00:28:34,647
[woman] He's going down.

444
00:28:38,939 --> 00:28:40,314
The city's picking sides.

445
00:28:40,397 --> 00:28:41,647
[Jess] Trick or treat.

446
00:28:45,647 --> 00:28:48,106
[crowd clamoring]

447
00:29:14,939 --> 00:29:17,397
Whatever happens tonight,
to them, to me, to you...

448
00:29:17,481 --> 00:29:20,772
Matt Murdock and Karen Page
never leave this building alive.

449
00:29:20,856 --> 00:29:23,064
Now, go do your jobs.

450
00:29:23,147 --> 00:29:25,606
Sir, Murdock's not alone.

451
00:29:26,522 --> 00:29:27,564
Ah.

452
00:29:31,272 --> 00:29:34,606
[Fisk] Well, if you're feeling challenged
by your responsibilities...

453
00:29:35,981 --> 00:29:38,564
feel free to tender your resignations.

454
00:29:42,022 --> 00:29:43,439
[officer] We'll take care of it, sir.

455
00:29:48,356 --> 00:29:50,814
-[crowd clamoring in distance]
-Can you hear it?

456
00:29:52,689 --> 00:29:55,147
Pretty soon everyone out there
will be in here.

457
00:29:56,147 --> 00:29:59,647
[sirens echoing,
men speaking indistinctly]

458
00:29:59,731 --> 00:30:01,314
[officer 1] Team Two, clear the hallways.

459
00:30:01,397 --> 00:30:03,397
-[officer 2] You heard him.
-[officer 1] Move out.

460
00:30:06,522 --> 00:30:07,939
The Task Force is coming.

461
00:30:10,272 --> 00:30:11,272
This is it.

462
00:30:19,356 --> 00:30:20,689
-[Karen] We'll be right here.
-[Kirsten] Mmm-hmm.

463
00:30:22,731 --> 00:30:23,731
Stay safe.

464
00:30:24,397 --> 00:30:25,481
You, too.

465
00:30:26,731 --> 00:30:28,564
-You ready?
-Finally.

466
00:30:34,272 --> 00:30:37,439
-[all chattering indistinctly]
-[sirens wailing]

467
00:30:52,564 --> 00:30:55,481
Make a hole. Make a-- Come on!
Get out of the way! Make a hole!

468
00:31:00,981 --> 00:31:04,981
All right, let's not do anything
that we're gonna regret later, all right?

469
00:31:05,064 --> 00:31:07,064
Put the guns down.

470
00:31:11,022 --> 00:31:13,481
Sir, it's the attorney general.

471
00:31:14,314 --> 00:31:15,772
He'd like to speak with you.

472
00:31:22,689 --> 00:31:25,814
Cherry, aren't you supposed to be upstate
playing bingo or some shit?

473
00:31:25,897 --> 00:31:28,272
-You don't fucking belong here.
-Yeah, we do.

474
00:31:28,356 --> 00:31:32,189
Or maybe you forgot, we serve the people,
not the other way around.

475
00:31:32,939 --> 00:31:35,231
Take one more step
and we'll shoot you right in the face.

476
00:31:35,314 --> 00:31:37,022
I'll be back.

477
00:31:40,356 --> 00:31:42,106
-Oh, Heather--
-Give me your jacket.

478
00:31:42,189 --> 00:31:44,064
Uh, oh, it's a Canali.

479
00:31:44,147 --> 00:31:45,731
He's shivering. Give it to me.

480
00:31:48,314 --> 00:31:50,272
It's just madness.

481
00:31:50,356 --> 00:31:52,481
Look, we... we are both reasonable people.

482
00:31:52,564 --> 00:31:55,189
There's no reason we should burn with him.

483
00:31:55,272 --> 00:31:56,606
-Ease up.
-[Cole] Just back up.

484
00:31:56,689 --> 00:31:58,772
-Everybody just back the fuck up!
-Shoot them.

485
00:31:58,856 --> 00:32:00,856
-Whoa, whoa.
-Tell him!

486
00:32:00,939 --> 00:32:02,856
Tell him about Hector Ayala!

487
00:32:02,939 --> 00:32:05,772
Hector Ayala was a fucking cop killer.

488
00:32:05,856 --> 00:32:09,314
-I said shoot that bastard.
-No! My husband wouldn't kill police.

489
00:32:13,481 --> 00:32:16,147
You told me Ayala
pushed men off the platform.

490
00:32:16,231 --> 00:32:17,564
I told you to shoot that guy.

491
00:32:18,731 --> 00:32:21,647
-[Cole] He's one of ours.
-He's not one of ours. He's one of them.

492
00:32:21,731 --> 00:32:22,981
The fuck happened to you?

493
00:32:23,064 --> 00:32:25,939
You lose your balls in that fire, too?
I gave you a direct fucking order.

494
00:32:26,022 --> 00:32:27,897
-No.
-Fine. You won't do it. I will.

495
00:32:27,981 --> 00:32:30,814
-I'll just fucking do-- [grunts]
-[crowd gasps]

496
00:32:31,814 --> 00:32:32,939
Get him outta here.

497
00:32:46,356 --> 00:32:47,522
Let them in.

498
00:32:47,606 --> 00:32:49,397
-All right!
-[Cole] Let them in. Move!

499
00:32:50,272 --> 00:32:51,814
Move! Let them in!

500
00:32:54,856 --> 00:32:57,439
Why don't you and I get out of here?

501
00:32:57,522 --> 00:32:59,481
[choking]

502
00:33:01,981 --> 00:33:03,689
Don't you ever touch me.

503
00:33:21,689 --> 00:33:22,981
Kill Fisk!

504
00:33:24,856 --> 00:33:26,606
[man] We're coming for you, Fisk!

505
00:33:26,897 --> 00:33:29,022
Take down Fisk! Take down Fisk!

506
00:33:29,106 --> 00:33:30,481
[crowd chanting] Bring us Fisk!

507
00:33:41,106 --> 00:33:42,689
-[grunts]
-[groans]

508
00:33:46,397 --> 00:33:48,022
-[officer groaning]
-[crowd] Bring us Fisk!

509
00:33:48,106 --> 00:33:49,647
Bring us Fisk!

510
00:33:49,731 --> 00:33:51,231
Bring us Fisk!

511
00:33:55,772 --> 00:33:56,772
I'm here.

512
00:34:01,981 --> 00:34:02,981
Okay.

513
00:34:06,231 --> 00:34:08,314
It's the office of the AG again.

514
00:34:08,397 --> 00:34:11,397
Final offer, he says, tender
your resignation and leave the city.

515
00:34:11,481 --> 00:34:12,939
Leave New York?

516
00:34:13,022 --> 00:34:15,939
And there I thought
I had your support, Sheila.

517
00:34:16,022 --> 00:34:19,147
The office of the mayor has my support.

518
00:34:19,231 --> 00:34:22,439
[crowd chanting]
Bring us Fisk! Bring us Fisk!

519
00:34:25,731 --> 00:34:31,356
Renounce your citizenship, go into exile,
and the AG promises not to prosecute.

520
00:34:31,439 --> 00:34:33,397
No! I won't leave this!

521
00:34:33,481 --> 00:34:36,606
[Sheila] Speak to him. This is
the best offer you are going to get.

522
00:34:36,689 --> 00:34:37,856
Open that door.

523
00:34:37,939 --> 00:34:39,481
[Sheila] There are lives at stake.

524
00:34:39,564 --> 00:34:40,814
Take the deal!

525
00:34:40,897 --> 00:34:41,939
Open it!

526
00:34:42,981 --> 00:34:45,106
Open that door!

527
00:34:46,689 --> 00:34:48,064
Boo!

528
00:34:48,147 --> 00:34:49,522
[grunts]

529
00:34:53,606 --> 00:34:56,314
[all screaming]

530
00:35:06,022 --> 00:35:08,356
[officers groaning]

531
00:35:14,731 --> 00:35:16,647
[screaming]

532
00:35:16,731 --> 00:35:19,189
No, no, no. No, no, no. No! No!

533
00:35:22,606 --> 00:35:23,772
[Fisk] Come on!

534
00:35:24,272 --> 00:35:25,814
[woman screams]

535
00:35:25,897 --> 00:35:28,522
[grunting]

536
00:35:40,564 --> 00:35:42,314
-[screams]
-Shh!

537
00:35:42,397 --> 00:35:44,439
[groans]

538
00:35:55,606 --> 00:35:57,564
[screaming]

539
00:36:10,814 --> 00:36:13,439
-[man groaning]
-[exhales]

540
00:36:26,564 --> 00:36:28,272
[groaning]

541
00:36:35,897 --> 00:36:38,022
[all chattering indistinctly]

542
00:36:47,106 --> 00:36:50,064
[people screaming in distance]

543
00:36:53,314 --> 00:36:55,189
[grunting]

544
00:37:05,897 --> 00:37:09,814
[crowd booing]

545
00:37:21,564 --> 00:37:23,356
You're wrong about me!

546
00:37:26,272 --> 00:37:27,439
You're wrong!

547
00:37:30,897 --> 00:37:33,064
I have done everything for you!

548
00:37:33,147 --> 00:37:35,522
I've given you my heart and my soul!

549
00:37:35,606 --> 00:37:36,772
Liar!

550
00:37:37,981 --> 00:37:40,564
-You're a liar!
-[crowd clamoring]

551
00:37:40,647 --> 00:37:43,439
I've fought for you, and I stand here now!

552
00:37:43,522 --> 00:37:44,772
And I still fight...

553
00:37:45,981 --> 00:37:47,856
No! No! Stop!

554
00:37:49,939 --> 00:37:51,939
[Daredevil] Listen! Listen!

555
00:37:52,022 --> 00:37:55,189
And I just wanted a better New York!

556
00:38:10,856 --> 00:38:12,647
[screams]

557
00:38:23,522 --> 00:38:25,022
[Daredevil] Stop!

558
00:38:44,731 --> 00:38:46,439
No! Stop!

559
00:38:53,772 --> 00:38:55,564
We're better than this!

560
00:38:55,647 --> 00:38:57,897
-Stay down, Fisk. Stay down!
-[Fisk grunting]

561
00:38:58,481 --> 00:39:00,772
No! [grunts]

562
00:39:03,897 --> 00:39:05,147
Listen. Listen to me.

563
00:39:05,731 --> 00:39:06,731
It's over.

564
00:39:08,106 --> 00:39:09,647
It's over for both of us.

565
00:39:12,397 --> 00:39:15,106
[Fisk panting manically]

566
00:39:19,939 --> 00:39:21,356
Take the deal.

567
00:39:22,897 --> 00:39:23,981
I will not.

568
00:39:25,356 --> 00:39:28,189
You go to prison,
you die locked away from her memory,

569
00:39:28,272 --> 00:39:31,064
or you do what you do,
and this whole thing starts over again.

570
00:39:31,606 --> 00:39:35,439
The poison, the fight, the death.

571
00:39:41,439 --> 00:39:44,189
This is your so-called retribution?

572
00:39:48,189 --> 00:39:49,689
It means nothing to me.

573
00:39:49,772 --> 00:39:50,814
What...

574
00:39:52,064 --> 00:39:53,231
What about grace?

575
00:39:54,064 --> 00:39:55,356
No, no, no, no.

576
00:39:56,064 --> 00:39:58,856
You are not allowed to offer that to me!

577
00:39:58,939 --> 00:40:01,731
I believe you love this city. Same as me.

578
00:40:01,814 --> 00:40:03,731
We have the opportunity to give it peace.

579
00:40:04,564 --> 00:40:06,147
Even if we have none.

580
00:40:07,481 --> 00:40:08,522
That's grace.

581
00:40:16,397 --> 00:40:18,522
[Fisk gasps]

582
00:40:27,564 --> 00:40:28,689
No.

583
00:40:31,814 --> 00:40:32,856
Please.

584
00:40:39,231 --> 00:40:40,231
No.

585
00:40:51,272 --> 00:40:52,272
I, uh...

586
00:40:55,772 --> 00:40:56,814
I accept--

587
00:41:05,189 --> 00:41:06,897
You'll understand if I don't...

588
00:41:07,814 --> 00:41:09,064
shake your hand?

589
00:41:12,522 --> 00:41:13,606
Yeah, Wilson.

590
00:41:14,439 --> 00:41:15,606
I understand.

591
00:41:29,106 --> 00:41:32,147
[♪ melancholy music playing]

592
00:42:05,272 --> 00:42:06,772
[Karen] I don't know,
it's just kind of...

593
00:42:07,564 --> 00:42:09,314
hard to believe it's really over.

594
00:42:11,981 --> 00:42:13,106
Yeah, I know.

595
00:42:14,272 --> 00:42:15,272
I know.

596
00:42:17,314 --> 00:42:18,814
This normal life thing is...

597
00:42:21,731 --> 00:42:25,147
No more running,
no more being hunted, no more...

598
00:42:25,231 --> 00:42:26,981
-[Karen] It's gonna be hard.
-It's really hard.

599
00:42:27,064 --> 00:42:28,481
-So hard.
-[Matt] Why is it so hard?

600
00:42:28,564 --> 00:42:30,689
-Because we're really messed up.
-[laughs]

601
00:42:30,772 --> 00:42:32,564
-[Karen] Are we really that messed up?
-What does that say about us?

602
00:42:32,647 --> 00:42:33,856
[Karen] My God.

603
00:42:37,231 --> 00:42:39,647
If I'm honest,
I'm not sure I know how to do it.

604
00:42:41,231 --> 00:42:43,147
Well, that's okay. Neither do I.

605
00:42:46,939 --> 00:42:48,731
I'd still like to take a shot at it.

606
00:42:49,606 --> 00:42:50,647
Yeah, me too.

607
00:42:53,647 --> 00:42:55,314
[sirens wailing]

608
00:43:11,606 --> 00:43:14,064
[Karen] I thought we'd have more time.

609
00:43:21,397 --> 00:43:23,814
[♪ ominous music playing]

610
00:43:26,064 --> 00:43:28,397
[officers chattering indistinctly]

611
00:43:37,897 --> 00:43:39,314
-Matthew Murdock?
-[Matt] Yes, sir.

612
00:43:39,397 --> 00:43:42,689
You're under arrest for assault,
attempted murder. And it's a long list.

613
00:43:42,772 --> 00:43:44,064
Daredevil's crimes?

614
00:43:44,147 --> 00:43:46,856
-[officer] You have the right to--
-Waive the advisement, not the rights.

615
00:43:48,356 --> 00:43:49,356
I used to be a lawyer.

616
00:43:58,272 --> 00:43:59,314
I love you.

617
00:44:00,356 --> 00:44:01,606
I love you too.

618
00:44:22,272 --> 00:44:24,522
[♪ melancholy rock playing,
Radiohead "Pyramid Song"]

619
00:44:24,606 --> 00:44:26,689
[vocalizing]

620
00:44:38,439 --> 00:44:42,981
♪ I jumped in the river, what did I see? ♪

621
00:44:48,272 --> 00:44:53,731
♪ Black-eyed angels swam with me ♪

622
00:44:55,981 --> 00:44:56,981
Daddy!

623
00:44:57,356 --> 00:45:01,647
♪ A moon full of stars and astral cars ♪

624
00:45:01,731 --> 00:45:03,897
Oh, I missed you so much.

625
00:45:05,439 --> 00:45:10,064
♪ And all the figures I used to see ♪

626
00:45:13,022 --> 00:45:14,022
[man] BB.

627
00:45:15,481 --> 00:45:16,897
I thought you should have this.

628
00:45:17,231 --> 00:45:19,814
-What's this?
-Welcome to the Bulletin.

629
00:45:23,814 --> 00:45:30,481
♪ All my past and futures ♪

630
00:45:32,689 --> 00:45:39,606
♪ And we all went to heaven
in a little row boat ♪

631
00:45:41,814 --> 00:45:46,481
♪ There was nothing to fear
and nothing to doubt ♪

632
00:45:46,564 --> 00:45:47,689
Are you okay?

633
00:45:49,606 --> 00:45:50,606
Yeah.

634
00:45:52,064 --> 00:45:53,064
The work was...

635
00:45:53,981 --> 00:45:55,314
different over there.

636
00:45:55,397 --> 00:45:56,481
And you're done?

637
00:45:57,897 --> 00:45:58,897
Yeah.

638
00:45:59,564 --> 00:46:02,022
I heard he found someone else.

639
00:46:02,564 --> 00:46:04,772
[woman] Mr. Robertson,

640
00:46:05,647 --> 00:46:08,981
I just wanted to congratulate you
on becoming a million miler.

641
00:46:10,189 --> 00:46:13,564
-Welcome to the club.
-Oh, wow.

642
00:46:25,689 --> 00:46:32,189
♪ Jumped into the river ♪

643
00:46:34,314 --> 00:46:39,481
♪ Black-eyed angels swam with me ♪

644
00:46:41,231 --> 00:46:46,106
[inmates chattering indistinctly]

645
00:46:46,189 --> 00:46:52,647
♪ A moon full of stars and astral cars ♪

646
00:46:52,731 --> 00:46:56,231
♪ And all the figures I used to see ♪

647
00:47:02,272 --> 00:47:06,981
♪ All my lovers were there with me ♪

648
00:47:10,064 --> 00:47:16,814
♪ All my past and futures ♪

649
00:47:19,231 --> 00:47:26,189
♪ And we all went to heaven
in a little row boat ♪

650
00:47:27,897 --> 00:47:33,106
♪ There was nothing to fear
and nothing to doubt ♪

651
00:47:36,397 --> 00:47:42,356
♪ There was nothing to fear
and nothing to doubt ♪

652
00:48:18,564 --> 00:48:20,939
[inmates chattering indistinctly]
